    <h1>QA Setup &amp; Processes</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>This page outlines the necessary tools, software, and processes =
required for QA setup at Hargreaves Lansdown, including how to request acce=
ss to systems, install tools, set up automation frameworks, and access test=
 environments.</p>
<h2 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-Programs/ToolstoRequest=F0=9F=9B=A0=EF=B8=
=8F">Programs/Tools to Request =F0=9F=9B=A0=EF=B8=8F</h2>
<p>To request the necessary software, use the links provided below. Ensure =
that your request is approved and processed before attempting to install or=
 configure any of the tools.</p>
<h3 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-1.AccesstoSharedDrives=F0=9F=93=82">1. <str=
ong>Access to Shared Drives</strong> =F0=9F=93=82</h3>
<p>Request access to the G:\ and F:\ drives for applications using the <em>=
Non-standard IT request</em> form:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Request Form</strong>: <a href=3D"https://hlprod.service-now.com=
/sp?id=3Dsc_cat_item&amp;sys_id=3D485659fe1b613410d0967558d34bcbcf&amp;sysp=
arm_category=3Dnull&amp;catalog_id=3D-1&amp;referrer=3Dpopular_items" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Non-standard IT Request</a></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-2.SoftwareInstallationRequests=F0=9F=92=BB"=
>2. <strong>Software Installation Requests</strong> =F0=9F=92=BB</h3>
<p>Use the <em>System Access</em> form to request the following application=
s:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>VMware Horizon / Horizon Client 2406</p></li>
<li>
<p>Brokerfocus v15.2</p></li>
<li>
<p>HL Focus</p></li>
<li>
<p>Toad for SAP 4.2.1</p></li>
<li>
<p>Postman 10.13.0</p></li>
<li>
<p>Putty 0.81</p></li>
<li>
<p>Node.JS =E2=86=92 For the <strong>Playwright Automation</strong> framewo=
rk.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Request Form</strong>: <a href=3D"https://hlprod.service-now.com=
/sp?id=3Dsc_cat_item&amp;sys_id=3Dd81e07d71bcdb01099a58594e34bcbed&amp;sysp=
arm_category=3Dnull&amp;catalog_id=3D-1&amp;referrer=3Dpopular_items" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">System Access Request</a></p>
<h2 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-InstallationofToolsonYourDevice=F0=9F=96=A5=
=EF=B8=8F">Installation of Tools on Your Device =F0=9F=96=A5=EF=B8=8F</h2>
<p>After your requests have been approved, the tools should appear as avail=
able for installation on your desktop. You can proceed by selecting the app=
lications to install directly from your desktop.</p>
<h2 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-TestCasesforAutomation=F0=9F=93=9D">Test Ca=
ses for Automation =F0=9F=93=9D</h2>
<h3 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-CreatingTestCases">Creating Test Cases</h3>
<p>Test cases should be created in advance of automation. It is recommended=
 to discuss the specific test cases with your team or manager via a call fo=
r further clarification. Test cases may be stored or documented in various =
locations, including project management tools or internal documentation rep=
ositories.</p>
<p>If you need assistance with where to find or create the test cases, plea=
se reach out to your lead or the QA team for guidance.</p>
<h2 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-PlaywrightAutomationFrameworkSetup=E2=9A=99=
=EF=B8=8F">Playwright Automation Framework Setup =E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F</h2>
<p>To set up the Playwright automation framework on your device, follow the=
se steps:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Access the Repository</strong>: You can clone the Playwright aut=
omation repository from GitLab using the following methods:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Clone with SSH</strong>:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git@git=
lab.com:hldev/hlweb/rrt/playwright-automation.git</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Clone with HTTPS</strong>:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">https:/=
/gitlab.com/hldev/hlweb/rrt/playwright-automation.git</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Clone the Repository</strong>: After selecting your preferred cl=
oning method, use Git to clone the repository to your local machine.</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p><strong>Set Up the Framework</strong>: Once cloned, follow the setup pro=
cess by reading and executing the instructions in the <code>Setup.txt</code=
> file, followed by the <code>README.txt</code> file.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-RequestinganIDE=F0=9F=96=B1=EF=B8=8F">Reque=
sting an IDE =F0=9F=96=B1=EF=B8=8F</h3>
<p>If you do not have an IDE installed, you may need to request one. Either=
 <strong>Visual Studio Code</strong> or <strong>IntelliJ</strong> is recomm=
ended for cloning the repository.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Request IDE</strong>: Please reach out to your IT department to =
request one of the supported IDEs.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-TestEnvironmentsforExploratoryTesting=F0=9F=
=94=8D">Test Environments for Exploratory Testing =F0=9F=94=8D</h2>
<p>To execute exploratory testing, ensure that you are pointing to the corr=
ect environment.</p>
<h3 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-AvailableTestEnvironments:">Available Test =
Environments:</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>QA Environment</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>QA Atlas</p></li>
<li>
<p><a href=3D"https://qa-online.hl.co.uk/my-accounts/login-step-one" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">QA Online</a></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Lower Test Environment</strong> (for deeper testing scenarios):<=
/p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href=3D"https://test9-online.hl.co.uk/my-accounts/login-step-one" cla=
ss=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Test 9 Online</a></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-RequestingAccesstoTestEnvironments">Request=
ing Access to Test Environments</h3>
<p>You can request access to the necessary test environments using the foll=
owing link:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Request Test Environments</strong>: <a href=3D"https://hlprod.se=
rvice-now.com/sp?id=3Dsc_cat_item&amp;table=3Dsc_cat_item&amp;sys_id=3D0c10=
32b81bed3c10d0967558d34bcb02" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Test=
 Environment Request</a></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-SwitchingEnvironmentsintheFramework">Switch=
ing Environments in the Framework</h3>
<p>You may need to change the target environment in the Playwright framewor=
k. This can be configured within the framework settings, where you can modi=
fy the environment URL.</p>
<h2 id=3D"QASetup&amp;Processes-Summary=F0=9F=93=8B">Summary =F0=9F=93=8B</=
h2>
<p>This page provides a comprehensive overview of the QA setup and tools yo=
u need to request, install, and configure as part of your workflow at Hargr=
eaves Lansdown. Ensure you have all necessary software, test cases, and env=
ironments set up before beginning automation or exploratory testing tasks.<=
/p>
<p>For additional questions or support, please reach out to your team lead =
or IT department.</p>
